config.script:
def showSpinner():
	    self.parent.parent.getChild("loading").position.display = True
	    self.parent.parent.getChild("data").position.display = False
	def hideSpinner():
	    self.parent.parent.getChild("loading").position.display = False
	    self.parent.parent.getChild("data").position.display = True

	logger = system.util.getLogger('lossReport')
	startTime = self.getSibling("timeSelector").props.params.timeStart
	endTime = self.getSibling("timeSelector").props.params.timeEnd
	selectedAreaID = self.view.custom.SelectedAreaID
	selectedLineID = self.view.custom.SelectedLineID
	selectedLossType = self.view.custom.SelectedLossType
	selectedShift = self.view.custom.SelectedShift
	selectedProductCode = self.view.custom.SelectedPC
	siteID = self.view.custom.SelectedSiteID
	queryPath = 'app/OEE/getReportLinesLossEventDetails'
	summaryPath = 'app/OEE/getReportLinesLossSummaryDetails'
	if selectedLossType == 'all': selectedLossType = ''
	if selectedAreaID == 0: selectedAreaID = ''
	if selectedLineID == 0: selectedLineID = ''
	if selectedProductCode == 'all': selectedProductCode = ''

	params = {
		'startTime': startTime,
		'endTime': endTime,
		'areaID': selectedAreaID,
		'lineID': selectedLineID,
		'type': selectedLossType,
		'siteID': siteID,
		'shift': selectedShift,
		'productCode': selectedProductCode
	}
	system.perspective.print(params)
	
	showSpinner()  # Start the spinner
	
	try:
	    results = system.db.runNamedQuery(queryPath, params)
	    summaryResults = system.db.runNamedQuery(summaryPath, params)
	    system.perspective.print(summaryResults)
	    self.view.custom.LineLossEvent = results
	    self.view.custom.LineLossSummary = summaryResults
	except Exception as Argument:
	    system.perspective.print(str(Argument))
	finally:
	    hideSpinner()  # Hide the spinner
